* Unix/POSIX compliance roadmap

* Core syscall ABI
    - [x] use Linux i386 syscall numbers where the ABI matches
    - [x] return negative errno values from new/updated kernel syscalls
    - [x] add userspace errno
    - [x] add libc wrappers that translate -errno to -1 and errno
    - [x] keep PolyOS-private syscall numbers in the 500+ range
    - [x] migrate remaining PolyOS-private syscalls behind debug/test APIs only
    - [x] route BSD socket libc wrappers through Linux i386 socketcall(102)
    - [x] route userspace sleep through nanosleep instead of PolyOS sleep
    - [x] route public reboot wrapper through Linux i386 reboot(88)
    - [x] expose semaphores through POSIX-like sem_init/sem_wait/sem_post/sem_destroy wrappers
    - [x] convert network and semaphore syscalls to precise -errno values

* Process model
    - [x] fork creates a new process
    - [x] waitpid writes Unix-style encoded exit status
    - [x] waitpid supports WNOHANG
    - [x] complete execve envp support
    - [x] keep zombies until waited and reparent orphan processes
    - [x] add kill syscall and Unix wait status for signal termination
    - [x] add sigaction/signal libc wrappers and SIGCHLD/SIGINT/SIGPIPE constants
    - [x] deliver userspace signal handlers with sigreturn
    - [x] send SIGCHLD on child exit
    - [ ] add process groups, sessions, foreground TTY

* File descriptors
    - [x] stdin/stdout/stderr start as fd 0/1/2
    - [x] fork shares open file descriptions
    - [x] add dup
    - [x] add dup2
    - [x] add fcntl with FD_CLOEXEC and F_DUPFD
    - [x] make exec close FD_CLOEXEC descriptors only
    - [x] add O_NONBLOCK status flag support
    - [x] add O_TRUNC and O_APPEND behavior
    - [x] pipe read returns EOF when writers are closed
    - [x] pipe write reports broken pipe when readers are closed
    - [x] wake blocked pipe readers/writers instead of polling

* Filesystem
    - [x] normalize ., .., repeated slash, and relative paths
    - [x] list direct VFS mount points in parent directories
    - [x] add per-process cwd
    - [x] add chdir
    - [x] add getcwd
    - [x] add mkdir
    - [x] add rmdir
    - [x] add unlink
    - [x] add getdents
    - [x] add libc readdir wrapper
    - [x] improve stat/fstat file type and mode bits
    - [x] add lstat
    - [x] reject rmdir on non-empty memfs directories with ENOTEMPTY
    - [x] avoid FAT truncate/flush on every write
    - [x] add chmod, chown, umask with real uid/gid later
    - [x] make FAT create/remove directory entries robust

* Shell / userspace utilities
    - [x] add builtins: help, cd, pwd, id, ls, cat, touch, cp, mv, mkdir, rmdir, rm, stat, chmod, echo
    - [x] make execve resolve relative paths with cwd
    - [x] make FAT directory names shell-friendly for short 8.3 entries
    - [x] hide dotfiles in ls by default and add ls -a
    - [x] add basic /bin and /bin/*.elf executable lookup
    - [x] add redirection: >, >>, <
    - [x] add pipelines with pipe/dup2
    - [x] add real PATH environment lookup instead of fixed /bin fallback
    - [x] add environment variables

* Memory
    - [x] add brk syscall
    - [x] add userspace sbrk
    - [x] move C malloc/free onto userspace sbrk
    - [x] migrate Rust userspace allocator away from PolyOS malloc syscall
    - [ ] add mmap, munmap, mprotect
    - [x] expand COW tests for heap, globals, stack, and fd state

* TTY / terminal
    - [x] expose console/screen/serial/keyboard devices through devfs
    - [x] add /dev/tty
    - [ ] add termios: tcgetattr, tcsetattr
    - [ ] add canonical/raw input modes
    - [ ] send SIGINT on Ctrl-C to the foreground process group

* Time
    - [x] timer interrupt and sleep syscall
    - [x] add nanosleep
    - [x] add clock_gettime
    - [x] add gettimeofday
    - [x] make sleep a libc wrapper over nanosleep

* Networking
    - [x] network device abstraction
    - [x] rtl8139 in QEMU
    - [x] DHCP, ARP, ICMP, DNS basics
    - [x] socket, sendto, recvfrom basics
    - [x] add bind, connect, listen, accept
    - [x] add send, recv, getsockname, getpeername, setsockopt
    - [ ] move DNS resolver behavior toward userspace libc

* Selftests
    - [x] userspace selftest program
    - [x] kernel selftest syscall for memory, paging, VFS, devfs, ELF loader
    - [x] selftest covers errno, brk/sbrk, dup/dup2, fcntl, O_TRUNC/O_APPEND, cwd, mkdir/rmdir/unlink, ENOTEMPTY, stat/lstat, getdents, opendir/readdir
    - [x] selftest covers fork, pipe, semaphore, waitpid, zombies, orphan reparenting, COW stack, environment variables
    - [x] optional selftest net mode covers DHCP and ping gateway
    - [ ] add automated host-side QEMU log checker
